data.description: Whole house has been professionally painted a neutral color. Brand new carpet too!!  This family has been relocated to Texas and motivated to sell! Guest room or in-law suite downstairs. Large spacious rooms with plenty of storage throughout this home. Shows better in person! With its expansive foyer, beautiful tile floors, and wainscoting, the hallway leads into the living room, dining area, and kitchen, adorned with trey ceilings, wainscoting, and crown molding. The generous living room with a gas fireplace and mantle that defines the space beautifully. The kitchen features a spacious center island, granite countertops, and a butler’s pantry for added counter space and storage. Great for a coffee/tea area also! The large formal dining room is ample for entertaining friends and family. Upstairs you will find the sprawling owner’s bedroom complete with trey ceilings and a sitting area perfect for a reading nook, tv room, exercise room, or flex space to meet your needs. The owner’s bath features double sinks, separate tub and shower, and multiple closets. The second floor is also home to three more spacious bedrooms as well as another full bathroom and walk-in laundry room. The covered patio and fully fenced in yard are perfect for enjoying warm summer evenings. The community pool offers enjoyment on hot summer days!Prime location close to amenities. Within minutes to Five Forks, downtown Simpsonville, and Woodruff Rd., shopping and dining are easily accessible. This beautiful home is spacious, functional, well appointed, and conveniently located!
